{{also|Symptom}}
==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈsɪm(p)təm/}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|σύμπτωμα||a happening, accident, symptom of disease|tr=sumptōma|lang=grc}}, from stem of {{term|συμπίπτω||Ι befall|tr=sumpiptō|lang=grc}}, from {{term|συν-||together|tr=sun-|lang=grc}} + {{term|πίπτω||I fall|tr=piptō|lang=grc}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|medicine|lang=en}} A [[perceived]] [[change]] in some [[function]], [[sensation]] or [[appearance]] of a [[person]] that [[indicates]] a [[disease]] or [[disorder]], such as [[fever]], [[headache]] or [[rash]].
# Anything that [[indicate]]s, or is [[characteristic]] of,  the [[presence]] of something else, especially of something undesirable.

